stic. Written for students, professors, and nonacademics alike, Screen Love is an accessible, provocative, and at times subversively funny read.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aGay menxSexual behavior. 0aGaysxSocial life and customs. 0aGaysxSocial networks. 0aInternet and gay men. 0aOnline dating. 0aSocial media. 4aCommunication : Communication. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848209540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438482095423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438482095/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles